# Run the Carthage installation tests on an iOS 26 simulator.
#
# `fastlane scan` otherwise defaults to the newest *pre-installed* simulator, which on the
# Xcode 26.5 CI image is an iOS 18.6 runtime. Running that old runtime under Xcode 26.5's
# CoreSimulator makes the simulator's networking hang, so `testCanFetchCustomerInfo` (a live
# backend call) deterministically times out. Pinning to `iPhone 17` forces an iOS 26.x runtime
# (the device doesn't exist on older iOS versions), matching the Xcode toolchain.
devices(["iPhone 17"])
